Arthur,<br><br>
I understand what you say, and I want both you and Humming Eagle to know that I too have derived a lot from this string.  We influence each other in ways perhaps unanticipated when we post here.  My post above, about the rivers of life and purification of the mind, was meant for those silent warriors who will be reading this string, but will not participate.<br><br>
Communication via written forms looses much of its content, but that which does come through may come through, or be percieved to come through, more as a shout than a conversation.  Humming Eagle, this may be where you are coming from when you talked about shouting.  I don't know.  <br><br>
But let me say that since I gave my wife the story about the Black and White Wolves inside each of us, and how we must feed one or the other, I have seen a significant change in her outlook on life.  For this, I am eternally greatful.  Because of my misfortune, my wife has been feeling bad for almost a year.  It hit her self-respect that I was fired.  She has to some extent withdrawn from a lot of activities since that event, and han been waiting for my situation to change.  She has been feeding the Black Wolf for many months.  We talked frequently about this, but it wasn't until I showed her your story that she really decided to begin living again.  She will continue to have her spells of darkness, but now I have an analogy to help her out.  <br><br>
You have given away a significant gift, and for doing so, this old ex-PJ will be eternally greatful.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


